Here are clear, manager-ready Datadog metric examples you can reference in your presentation. These show what visibility was missing and how Datadog addresses it in practical terms.

Datadog Metrics to Improve TDE Visibility
1. Encryption / Decryption Progress Tracking

Metrics & Signals:

SQL Server background task duration

Long-running internal processes

Database file read/write latency during encryption

Datadog Use Case:

Dashboard showing encryption progress trends correlated with I/O and CPU usage

Alerts when encryption throughput drops below expected thresholds

Management Value:
Real-time understanding of progress instead of manual estimation.

2. CPU Utilization During Encryption

Metrics:

system.cpu.user

system.cpu.system

SQL Server process CPU usage

Datadog Use Case:

Track CPU spikes caused by encryption scans

Validate that encryption load stays within acceptable limits

Management Value:
Prevents unexpected performance degradation during maintenance windows.

3. Disk I/O Impact and Throughput

Metrics:

Disk read/write latency

Disk queue length

IOPS per data and log volume

Datadog Use Case:

Identify I/O bottlenecks slowing encryption/decryption

Correlate slow encryption with storage performance

Management Value:
Enables accurate timeline forecasting and root-cause analysis.

4. TempDB Activity Monitoring

Metrics:

TempDB data and log file growth

TempDB write latency

Allocation waits related to tempdb

Datadog Use Case:

Early detection of tempdb contention caused by TDE

Prevents secondary performance issues during encryption

Management Value:
Reduces risk of unexpected system-wide impact.

5. Database-Level Health Indicators

Metrics:

Active connections

Blocking sessions

Long-running queries

Datadog Use Case:

Ensure business workloads remain stable during encryption

Immediate alerting if user impact occurs

Management Value:
Maintains service reliability during security changes.

6. Alerting & Executive Visibility

Datadog Dashboards & Alerts:

Alert if encryption-related CPU or I/O exceeds thresholds

Timeline view correlating encryption activity with system metrics

Management Value:
Provides leadership with confidence, transparency, and faster decision-making.

